\begin{tcbProblem}[label={problem:0061:question:Eng}]
	Triangle, square, pentagonal, hexagonal, heptagonal, and octagonal numbers are all figurate (polygonal) numbers and are generated by the following formulae:
	\begin{align*}
		\relax &\text{Triangle}   & {P}_{3 \mathcomma n} &\equal n \lparen n \mathplus 1 \rparen \fracslash 2 & \relax & 1 \mathcomma 3 \mathcomma  6 \mathcomma 10 \mathcomma 15 \mathcomma \unicodecdots \\%
		\relax &\text{Square}     & {P}_{4 \mathcomma n} &\equal { n }^{ 2 }                                  & \relax & 1 \mathcomma 4 \mathcomma  9 \mathcomma 16 \mathcomma 25 \mathcomma \unicodecdots \\%
		\relax &\text{Pentagonal} & {P}_{5 \mathcomma n} &\equal n \lparen 3n \minus 1 \rparen \fracslash 2   & \relax & 1 \mathcomma 5 \mathcomma 12 \mathcomma 22 \mathcomma 35 \mathcomma \unicodecdots \\%
		\relax &\text{Hexagonal}  & {P}_{6 \mathcomma n} &\equal n \lparen 2n \minus 1 \rparen                & \relax & 1 \mathcomma 6 \mathcomma 15 \mathcomma 28 \mathcomma 45 \mathcomma \unicodecdots \\%
		\relax &\text{Heptagonal} & {P}_{7 \mathcomma n} &\equal n \lparen 5n \minus 3 \rparen \fracslash 2   & \relax & 1 \mathcomma 7 \mathcomma 18 \mathcomma 34 \mathcomma 55 \mathcomma \unicodecdots \\%
		\relax &\text{Octagonal}  & {P}_{8 \mathcomma n} &\equal n \lparen 3n \minus 2 \rparen                & \relax & 1 \mathcomma 8 \mathcomma 21 \mathcomma 40 \mathcomma 65 \mathcomma \unicodecdots %
	\end{align*}
	The ordered set of three 4-digit numbers: 8128, 2882, 8281, has three interesting properties.
	\begin{enumerate}[label={\arabic*.}]
		\item The set is cyclic, in that the last two digits of each number is the first two digits of the next number (including the last number with the first).
		\item Each polygonal type: triangle (\( {P}_{3 \mathcomma 127} \equal 8128 \), square (\( {P}_{4 \mathcomma 91} \equal 8281 \)), and pentagonal (\( {P}_{5 \mathcomma 44} \equal 2882 \)), is represented by a different number in the set.
		\item This is the only set of 4-digit numbers with this property.
	\end{enumerate}
	Find the sum of the only ordered set of six cyclic 4-digit numbers for which each polygonal type: triangle, square, pentagonal, hexagonal, heptagonal, and octagonal, is represented by a different number in the set.
	\par%
